Package: raveR
Title: Transform R Scripts into Deep House Music
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nim", "Voltalino", email = "nim.voltalino@proton.me", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Stal", "Vedro", role = "ctb")
)
Description: Transform R scripts into listenable deep house music. Analyzes
    code structure (functions, control flow, complexity) and maps it to
    musical parameters to generate deterministic audio output. Supports
    multiple genres, live coding with file watching, and WAV/MP3 export.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/voltalino/raveR
BugReports: https://github.com/voltalino/raveR/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Imports:
    tuneR,
    audio,
    av,
    cyclocomp,
    digest,
    later,
    R6,
    watcher
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    seewave
Config/testthat/edition: 3
SystemRequirements: FFmpeg (for MP3 export)
